Some variables are standardized and so you'll see this format:

<TypeVariable>_<TypeReturn><NameVariable> Ex: txt_bCreate

List of possible names:

Type Variable:
scr (screen)
str (string)
stm (stream)
txt (files)
gl (opengl)
form (form)
tm (time)
tmr (timer)
err (error)
log (logs)
ncs (ncscript)
msg (messagebox)
ex (exception)
res (resource files)
net (network)
xin (xinput)
mtx (matrix)
cam (camera)
pkg (package)
trs (translate)
th (thread)
sha (shader)

Type Return:
b (bool)
i (int or INDEX)
f (float)
s (string)
t (prototype class)
r (resource file)
e (exception)
n (enumeration)
a (array)
l (list)
m (memory stack)
// t (time) //?epoch? > int
p (point)
x (input)
y (byte aka unsigned char)
u (unsigned int)
<nothing> (funcion void)

Name Variable is a short description about the variable
